article.headline: Nicholls St. 52, SE Louisiana 50
article.story: THIBODAUX, La. -- Anatoly Bose scored 14 points in the second half and Nicholls State rallied for a 52-50 win over Southeastern Louisiana on Saturday. Nicholls State (15-9, 8-4 Southland Conference) trailed 45-38 with 7:52 left to play, before going on a 12-5 run to tie the game. Bose capped the run on a 3-pointer to tie the score at 50-50 with 36 seconds left. Ryan Bathie broke the tie on two free throws with 21 seconds left for the final score. Southeastern Louisiana (9-14, 3-7) led 30-22 at halftime, thanks to 61.1 percent shooting (11 of 18) in the first half and 14 points from Damon Forest. Forest scored just one point in the second half, while the Cowboys hit 50 percent of their 3-pointers (6 of 12) in the half. Bathie paced Nicholls State with 23 points, including going 5-for-10 from the 3-point line. Patrick Sullivan added 13 points for the Lions.
